Installation
============

settings_env.py configuration sample
------------------------------------

DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.postgresql_psycopg2',
        'NAME': 'zenon',
        'USER': 'zenon',
        'HOST': '127.0.0.1',
    },
    'legacy_individual_subscription': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
        'NAME': 'zenon',
        'USER': 'zenon',
        'PASSWORD': 'zenon',
        'HOST': 'localhost',
    }
}

DATABASE_ROUTERS = ['individual_subscription.router.LegacyRouter']  # NOQA


Use
===

Migrate abonnes
---------------

python manage.py individual_subscription import_abonnes

Link abonnes
------------

Linking is done from CSV files (which could be exploded in several xls files)

pip install csvkit

in2csv Wikipedia1.xls >> wikipedia.csv 
in2csv Wikipedia2.xls >> wikipedia.csv 

python manage.py individual_subscription link_abonnes wikipedia.csv


